    <stitle>TRW MANUAL STEERING GEAR - DISASSEMBLE - WORM AND BEARINGS FROM HOUSING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="0">
        <title>WORM AND BEARINGS FROM HOUSING</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove worm cover bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove worm cover.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove shims. Discard the two rubber-coated embossed shims.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove worm bearing adjusting cup and roller bearing retainer assembly by pressing or
                pulling on end of column as required.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If bearing adjusting cup cocks, do not use force; tap bearing cup back in place and repeat
                        procedure.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove worm and input shaft assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove other roller bearing retainer assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and discard seals.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Do not remove the worm bearing cup, the bearings or, if included, the expansion plug that
                are pressed into housing unless they must be replaced. Filler or drain plug need not be removed except
                for replacement.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s05014_HL0501402.xml" xrefid="hl0501402">REPAIR</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
